author: Norly C
reviewBody: Going to update my review to be fair. Initially thought I got scammed and panicked. I had to report to Just Eat and contacted the restaurant themselves. They keep promising different delivery times that are never met. What's frustrating was, they marked my order as "delivered" even though I did not receive it. Out of panic, I ordered a new cake from The Eggfree Cake Box which is better btw. Now, I ended up with 2 huge cakes which are so unnecessary because I tried to cancel and open an order dispute. Maybe Just Eat contacted them directly and reported the incident because they had to take a photo of my door number lol. At the end of the day, they failed to deliver on time and failed to assure me since their support told me different things. For that reason, I still wouldn't recommend it. If you can't deliver when you say you will deliver, please DO NOT ACCEPT THE ORDER AND MARK IT DELIVERED. It's completely unfair since this is a meaningful cake for us and I wasn't even sure if I was going to get my cake or not. The cake itself is okay though. The icing tastes rich and it's spongy enough.

address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: Kelly s
reviewBody: ZERO STARS for this company. I ordered cakes and a number 8 balloon for my nieces birthday. I checked to make sure all in stock and was assured it would be delivered ok. I happened to be on FaceTime with my niece when the driver arrived, balloon was missing. My sister caught the driver before he drove off and when questioned he said he wasn’t given a balloon, just cakes. I contacted the company on live chat, What’s App and email and was told it had been escalated to a manager. Days later no response, chased again to get a short response of “it’s being looked into”. I work in customer service and distribution- it does not take 1 week to check stock to see if an extra balloon is on the shelf. Their service is absolutely appalling, they are constantly online on WhatsApp but are ignoring my messages. As a result of this I’m writing to the financial services ombudsman, looking at past reviews it’s a common issue. I personally would not order from them again
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: Rupinder KAUR
reviewBody: The experience I had for a week in Cakes Today, I've learnt so much. The staff are amazing especially the owner. As a team they work tremendously hard to keep the business running. author: Harin Vaghela
reviewBody: Where do I start with this unprofessional business?! I ordered a cake for valentines day 2 weeks beforehand for delivery on Valentines day by 8pm. At midday of the day of delivery I phoned them and asked what time the order is due but they cannot give me a delivery slot. At 8pm we still get nothing and I send an email only to be called back straight away to say they 'just found out' that my delivery was delayed and it will be with me by 10pm. At 10pm I still have nothing and of course no one is picking up the phone. At 11:15pm (!!) I get a call from the driver saying he still 30-45mins away! It seems like the company gave him too many deliveries and he said he still had lots more deliveries to go. I told the poor guy not to make the trip because it was too late for us anyway. I have tried to call 3 times to speak to someone with no luck and when I eventually get a call back the staff member is not allowed to issue refunds or cannot explain why this happened! Luckily I paid by PayPal so have raised a resolution through them now. In short, I wouldn't EVER use this company again and wouldn't recommend anyone else do so either.

author: Hristian Hristov
reviewBody: Had a cake order to be delivered for my birthday. I was out to the nearby supermarket when I got a call that the driver had been waiting for 20 minutes. We have a concierge so we asked to leave with the concierge if they don't want to wait 10 minutes for us to get back. We came back to find out that no one had rang our doorbell (digital system which records missed calls/door bell ringing). Concierge was also there the whole time and if they weren't there is a huge-font phone number on the entrance door to contact them. They had no missed calls and nobody had called them. After calling the company I had multiple people talking to me and almost an hour of explaining that their claims are just impossible. They were claiming that driver was there and there was no concierge, no phone number to ring and that they "tried" to contact us, but didn't explicitly say they rang the door bell (I kept reminding them we had no missed call or anything like that). Customer Service person kept insisting that we should pay 10£ for redelivery which I pushed back on as I was not provided a single piece of proof that driver was actually at my address. Redelivery was scheduled as a "one time exception" without having to pay extra. I was told I would get a text message and also a call when the driver is at my place. Needless to say, no phone call, no text, no door bell ringing (I was home all afternoon and evening and received 5 different packages from Amazon, one other delivery company and a local restaurant). Concierge also had no notifications or anything like that. I had to call the next day as it was already after working hours. Calling the next day I got the exact same excuses and also claims that there are pictures taken by the driver. Upon asking to see the pictures I was told they are for internal use only. I asked for any other proof - phone call to me, concierge. Any ask of proof was met with a blatant - "we tried delivery two times and we couldn't do it". I ended up asking for some sort of refund and after push back they finally offered 50% value voucher on their website... Like I would ever order from a service failing delivery twice. This whole time I had explained multiple times that if the driver used the post code only it was possible they were 1 block away as Google Maps has issues if they used Google Maps. I had provided the full address for the exact reasons and had never had any issues with any other delivery. After pointing out that a few more times and refusing the absurd "refund" my complaint was finally routed to a manger and I got 70% of my money back. Wasted 2 hours in total and I'm never thinking of using this place again. Even though I got a partial refund, I am thinking of researching customer rights and filing a signal with authorities. I see many people here having the same customer experience often without the nerves to endure endless discussion to finally get the deserved refund. That should be illegal especially the part where they refuse to give you proof of delivery claiming it's internal For the Cakes Today person replying to all 1-star reviews, ON was 128858 so instead of answering something generic I would love to see something more specific written down here for all people to see how much you "care" about your customers
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: A Khan
reviewBody: I read previous reviews and saw that on quite a few occasions the cake people ordered was wrongly produced. I thought I would give the company a chance as they didn't seem too bad from the outset. Mothers birthday happened to be on my Mothers actual birthday day. I ordered the cake well in advance of her birthday and due to the recent Virus Pandemic I emailed the company a few days before requesting for them to confirm if they can still facilitate my order which they said they could. On the day I was suppose to receive the cake it didn't arrive. Called the company and they advised due to shortages of staff they cant get my order to me until very late in the evening. The order came extremely late (8.30 PM). The birthday celebrations were ruined and cake was wasted. Additionally the cake colour was completely wrong. The cake was suppose to be grey in colour to match a diet coke theme, however it was white. I've asked for a partial refund and have just called to be advised that the manager isn't available for a week and that I have to wait a week to receive a response in relation to my last 2 emails requesting for reimbursement due to the stress and Inconvenience that was caused by the failure of the company to deliver the cake on time and over promising a service. I will update this review accordingly with any progress I have with my reimbursement claim but it was a dreadful experience and I certainly regret it. Update: 3rd April 2020 I am lost for words, still haven't received a refund the company hasn't accepted their failure and they lie. For example they promised to get my refund request escalated to a manger and they didn't do this. I've wasted almost 2 weeks waiting for a refund. Avoid this company at all cost they're fraudsters and liars. I will be contacting trading standards. Response to owner: 112715 is the order/invoice ref
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: koko red
reviewBody: By far the worst “chocolate” cake I have ever tasted! I rarely write online reviews but this experience was just so bad that I felt I should warn anyone who’s thinking of using this company. I’m truly AMAZED at all the positive feedback I’ve read on here but other sites are not so favourable so I would recommend that any one considering ordering a cake should do their research before handing over their hard earned cash to this company. I also find it strange how you can’t leave feedback on their own website? Why wouldn’t a good company allow you to leave feedback about their cakes on their own website??? I scored it 1 as 0 wasn’t an option and in its defence the presentation looked great (just like the enticing glossy photo on the website) but the taste can only be described as vile! I ordered the strawberry & chocolate sprinkles cake for my daughters 8th birthday party. What a huge disappointment it was. There was ZERO chocolate taste, the sponge was dry & it was layered with a strange whipped like creamy substance that tasted very synthetic. It also left an horrendous soapy after taste in the mouth. I tried to make the best of a bad situation & ended up serving very small slices with a big dollop of ice cream & lots of strawberries to mask the taste but even then most of the cake was left on the plates, even a bunch of kids didn’t want it!! It really spoiled that part of the celebrations as my daughter had been so excited to get her chocolate sprinkle cake & I could see she was disappointed. I was gutted I hadn’t researched this company in more depth before wasting my £50! Even the chocolate cakes from the supermarkets taste far superior to this shocking cake. How they managed to make it taste quite so bad is actually a skill in itself! The response from the company was also a joke, after telling them just how bad the cake was, the best they could do was offer me some kind of silly credit for the next cake I order from them- (free fruit toppings or something similar). Talk about adding insult to injury. It appears they do not care about customer satisfaction as I was assured by the tele-sales operator that one of the manager’s would directly contact me the same day but two weeks later and I have still not spoken to a manager. To be honest this after care service doesn’t surprise me as the cake was so awful it seems fitting that the follow up customer service would also be appalling. How this company is still in business amazes me??!!! Please save your money & AVOID, AVOID, AVOID, this dreadful company.
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: Jasmin Patel
reviewBody: The worst customer service I have ever experienced!!! Twice now I've had an issue with delivery times, communication and their customer service. During lockdown I have been sheilding, so decided the best way to celebrate my loved ones special days is by sending them a treat. I used Cakes Today through uber eats to deliver a cake to my gran and mistakenly decided even after an initial bad experience with delivery times, that I'd give them a second chance to send brownies to my young 10 year old cousin. On both occasions I pre-ordered the cake the night before for an afternoon delivery. Cakes Today happy accepted the order with no query regarding the time. On the actual day I had a notification from ubereats that the cakes had been delivered, so I called both to wish them a happy birthday and neither order had been delivered yet. I call cakes today, who then spent from the afternoon till after 10 pm in the evening promising me delivery of these cakes 'within an hour'. Not once did anyone contact me to tell me that there may be a delay, instead I had to spend my time chasing the whole day and being told 'sorry, it'll be with them in an hour' until 10pm or later on both occasions, with more than 24 hours notice!! What exactly is my gran of 83 and cousin of 10 going to do with birthday cakes at 10pm, on a weekday? On top of the poor excuses for the delays not once did I hear from Luke or Bianca (the unfortunate people that work for Cakes Today with no supervision apparently) a way to rectify the situation or keep my custom in some way by offering any goodwill gestures. They just continued to blame a dispatch manager, who they apparently don't have a personal number for and contact through some interesting messaging device that uses a code...(I think he was talking about a cellular device maybe or maybe another lie that he was trying to conjure up on the spot. Bianca had some interesting ones too, but we'll save those) It's now 10.15pm and my cousins cakes have still not been delivered, she will now be going to bed without her surprise and my aunt and uncle will have to stay up until Cakes Today decide to make a delivery. Uber Eats and any other platforms should ban them as partners. Complete shambles..a company driven by greed over customer satisfaction. There are plenty of other options out there, if you want quality with good service, try elsewhere. P.S It is now the next morning, the brownies were never delivered to my little cousin. No call or messages from cakes today have been received to let me know. No manager has called me back even after requesting it.
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

reviewBody: Ordered cake for 80 pounds for next day delivery. They did not deliver by 8pm despite me calling them to double check at 7pm. Agreed to reschedule same day by 10 pm and they forced me to pay extra 10 pounds as well. Of course, nothing delivered by 10 pm and now no one is picking up the phone either. No idea what to do. You would think that in current COVID 2021 businesses have figured out how to deliver goods/services – but not these guys. Generally hard to believe anyone can run a business like that. author: Sereggor
reviewBody: Worst costumer service ever seen. I ordered one cake for san valentines and because I'm working during the nights I wanted the cake around 12:00-13:00 or before, because I'm going to bed at 14:00. They called me the day before to confirm it at 16:00 waking me up, but i was happy because the cake suppose to be on time the next day. The cake arrives at 19:30 braking all my plans, the delivery guy with a really bad behaviour didn't want to deliver the cake to my door house (2nd floor) and I had to go to pick it downstairs. The cake came without strawberries and the the message, instead to be written on the cake it was down on the plate. I didn't want to write a review but today one of the managers called me for NOTHING. She just called me liar because they don't confirm hours(so what's the point to order a cake for an expecial ocasion like birthday or san valentines if the cake is not going to arrive in time?) And the delivery guy didn't came upstair, according to her for the COVID, to avoid physical contact ???. So what's the difference to pick the cake from his hand downstairs or upstairs? Come on. And because the cake came without strawberries and the message in the wrong side, and just because of that, they offered me 20% discount for the next cake??? Are you kidding? I'm not going to order again. If someone is going to order for an expecial ocasion please, consider another options. I paid £90 but I'm not going to do the same mistake again.

author: Ruth Ilton
reviewBody: Emese at Cakes Today, thank you so much for baking our beautiful cake! It was delicious! I was super happy with the service from Cakes Today. I couldn't believe you can even order same-day! I ordered next-day and it really was great value. The team contacted me to confirm the order over the phone. The 6-inch cake is listed as 'mini' but really was a great size! So tasty - the icing was light and fluffy and not overwhelming, great choice of chocolate toppings and the sponge was moist but light. Really delicious. The only comment I have is that the cake arrived around 20.45 (latest is supposed to be 20.00) but it was no problem as it keeps for a couple of days in the fridge. Recommend ordering for the next day to avoid this. Overall I can't recommend Cakes Today enough, I will use them again and recommend them to friends. Thank you.

reviewBody: I ordered the choc mini cake to a friend in Sutton. She enjoyed the cake and loved the surprise. The online ordering process had glitches during payment which made me redo few times. Finally I had to open Chat for someone to get back and was quickly responded to. The order was taken on the phone and quite professionally. The delivery had a glitch as my number was given to the driver and delivery notes were not passed on, so I had to text my friend's number to the driver when he arrived. Cake was delivered in perfect condition. So if they rectify ordering n delivery instruction issues this would be a 5* review from me. Will use again.

reviewBody: I ordered a cake for delivery on February 13 and was later informed that I couldn’t get the cake delivered even though the website doesn’t state if there is a minimum delivery requirement. Mind you I ordered the cake from the US and they ruined her surprise...how nice but I had no expectations they’d know. A little consideration goes a long way. Then after the 4th call they told me I had to purchase a card which I did however when the cake was delivered it didn’t receive the card that I paid for. It seems very strange that they later requested a minimum payment but wouldn’t even send me the cake with the card and when I did pay for the card I didn’t even receive the card. The phone lines kept dropping when I tried to make this complaint and it didn’t seem like they wanted to help me at all. Not sure if they will resolve this issue or not.

author: Laxmi
reviewBody: I was buying a cake for my daughter's birthday and the guy gave me a price £20 higher than listed on a food delivery app. After I pointed this out he said okay and told me there's a £9 delivery charge. After I enquired further why it was this much especially considering distance he told me delivery was free between 5-10pm which I agreed to. However it did not arrive during this time and people had to leave disappointed without cake. There was no sign of the cake on its way until afterwards when it arrived at 10.30pm. The box arrived with the sides fully open and the top loose and torn. When asking about this, the employee simply told me it was fully closed, as if my eyes were faulty, which is careless and unsafe particularly considering the pandemic. He wasn't listening and didn't seem to care but I still kept everyone's hopes up on the cake. All I can say is there was more cream than cake, with the top particularly cream heavy and uneven, there was no cake to put the candle in and for a cake with so much cream the sides were left thin and unappealing. The taste was not that great nor the aesthetic. It was small and placed firmly in the middle of the box and somehow the inside had it smeared across all sides. For a freshly made cake there sure is a lot of e-numbers. You are better off buying from a place elsewhere, the employees don't care and its not worth the money nor time.
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: Achala
reviewBody: Cakes Today understand good customer service is just as important as is the cake itself. Always striving to learn and make changes I have found it refreshing to have the opportunity to meet with the founders of the company and ask us what they do well and what they could do better. I first ordered cakes with them a good few years ago - the pricing and delivery commitment was an instant thumbs up from me...and so when I tastes the cakes being so light and yum it became our go to place to order cakes for celebrations, events, thank yous etc. They really work with the customer to deliver the cake and experience desired. Going above and beyond is ingrained in company culture I think as even if I have called last minute and than had a number of changes to end product they have patiently worked with me to deliver. Be it corporate requirement and or a personal family birthday cake...you get the feeling your custom is much valued and appreciated. If you are left feeling any less they strive to do their best to rectify. Cakes Today is a company I would recommend as the both the product and customer service are great. I would say order and try the service and experience it for yourself.
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: Amit K Thp
reviewBody: They basically robbed my money. I have been charged twice once from my amazon pay and once from my debit card. On September when it was my birthday I tried paying for my birthday cake via Amazon pay and after the transaction it showed me an error page, didn't see any confirmation page after or an email. Only I didn't know at the time that my payment has actually gone through. I only found out after about a month when the amazon pay finally sent me an email about it. Well at the time, after the amazon pay error, I proceeded to do pay again only this time around via my debit card. Payment went through as expected, I got my cake that day which was actually quite lovely. But when I received an email, around end of October, about the amazon pay, that went through for Cakes today, well I was bloody surprised because I have been charged again. Well amazon said since the money had already been processed and went through to the vender they can't do much. So I contacted Cakes today and they are refusing to give me back my £55 which they don't have any bloody rights to take it from me. Although the cake was good the appalling customer service, treating me like a fraud for asking my own money. How is that even fair? If I could give them 0 stars I would.
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: Iman Omar
reviewBody: From a previous positive experience, I relied on cakes today to deliver a cake and balloons to a friends house for their birthday. I was very hopeful that all would go well and be delivered on time. The delivery did indeed make it on time however instead of the balloons 2 and 1 my friend was presented with the numbers 1 and 0. I was disappointed but understood that mistakes can be made so I called back and was ensured that the correct number would be delivered within 3 hours. I was again met with disappointment when at that time I had received no confirmation text that the driver was on their way. Following up on this, I decided to call the shop where I was told to wait and they would call me back. Time passed and I still had not received a call. At this point I was utterly disappointed, I called once again and was told that the delivery would be made by 6:30pm. Although I wasn't hopeful that this time would be met I accepted their efforts and continued waiting. Once it reached 6:30 pm and no delivery had been made I was beyond angry. Despite my continuous patience and trust in the company and their staff, I was being told lies. At this point, I received a call from who I believe to be the manager. This is the one staff that spoke to me as a customer and apologised for the late deliveries and ensured delivery at a set time. Sure enough, the delivery was then made at 7:30 pm!!!!. Overall, I am quite disappointed with the service the only person I was ensured by was the manager but staff should be able to handle issues and apologies for inconveniences. Managers should not need to step in to resolve issues and be the ones apologising. I suggest better training on your staff to handle these types of issues AND PEOPLE NEED TO READ WHAT BALLOONS HAVE BEEN ORDERED BEFORE DELIVERING. Another customer may not be as patient as I had been. IT SHOULD NEVER take 6 hours to deliver one balloon to a house 15 minutes from the shop. I suggest careful thinking of what you’re promising to the customer before promising it
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: Kieran O'Rourke
reviewBody: I recently ordered a cake for a special occasion for my child. The staff were friendly, knowledgeable and had excellent recommendations for cake styles and designs. With their professional help I chose a lovely design. The delivery day and time slot were absolutely accurate. They even agreed to deliver on a Saturday evening! The service was first rate. When I got the cake it was beautiful. It was securely packed and well-protected. Due. solely to my own error (not any fault of Cakes Today), I had missed out some wording on the cake. To be honest, on a Sunday morning I expected little hope of being able to add some wording to the design. However, I then realised that Cakes Today is open on a Sunday. I called them first thing on Sunday morning and a member of staff was so helpful, bearing in mind that this was completely down to my own omission. They suggested that I pop over that Sunday morning and that they would try and help add some extra wording to the cake for me. When I arrived, the staff were brilliant and so helpful, despite my embarrassment of missing out wording on the cake. They even asked me what words and colours I wanted adding. They added the words in beautiful lettering in about 10 minutes. What is more, they didn't even look to charge me. Amazing! Needless to say, the cake tasted absolutely delicious. All I can say is that Cakes Today produce gorgeous and scrumptious cakes, and that their service is second to none! If this review is helpful, please give it a thumbs up. Thank you.

reviewBody: I am super impressed with CakesToday customer service. I ordered the cake on Uber eats at 9:30am and confirmed the cake will be delivered in hour. I told the lady about my predicament and she said she couldn't guarantee the delivery time but she can add the notes on the system to say this is urgent. I was furious cause the cake was for my Mum’s birthday and I needed the cake in time for a dinner reservation. I mentioned that Uber eats said this will be delivered in an hour but the lady said this is a glitch with Uber that they still rectifying it. Anyway, long story cut short. Cakes Today priotised my delivery and it arrived at 11:30am, just before I had to leave to organise my mums bday!!! This was such relief!! And I want to thank the lady (wish I took her name) and Cakes Today for such a wonderful service and consideration!!! I highly recommend them again and again! This is the 2nd time I have ordered cakes from this company and I was amazed how their cakes taste from the first order. Even the guests who tasted the cake was very complimentary. So that's why ordered from them again! Cakes Today have exceeded another level in my books!!! They deserve 5stars and a great review! Big thanks Maica ;)

author: Rukes Of London
reviewBody: very bad service please avoid I called and ordered a cake at 1:30 pm for my wifes birthday and was told that my cake would arrive anytime between 3pm to 8pm. I was a bit hesitant of ordering a cake for delivery as i usually pick my cakes up from my local baker but as i was stuck for time due last minute running around i thought this service would be convenient. I had family round for dinner and everyone obviously waiting on desert to only get a call at 8pm saying my drivers running late. The cake got here at 9:15pm ber in-mind this place is literally 4 miles from my house. They obviously made every excuse under the sun. Everyone left before the cake arrived and we ate it the next day. Do not let these people ruin your special day and pick up your cake from your local baker. They Charged me £35.99 for a 10 inch cake which tasted like a £3.99 iceland chocolate le gatteo. My local baker charges £18 for 12inch cake which tastes way better. To be honest the price wasn't an issue as they where delivering it, therefore i can see why they're pricey but it doesn't make sense if they don't meet their own deadlines they set themselves. So I really felt ripped off, I spoke to a manger requested a refund to be only told he will try to credit me on a next cake. I obviously won't be ordering again so whats the point of him trying credit me for a free cake and again the word trying, didn't also make sense. When they can just issue a refund instead. As you can tell their customer service skills aren't up to scratch. Basically these people deal with your special days and if you don't want them ruined, don't order here. I use own and run a sushi cafe with a delivery service and when we ran late we use to give customers 10%-20% on there order and on extreme cases like this one the order would be free. Obviously by my experience with this place, their crooks dressed as bakers. AVOID LIKE THE PLAGUE
name: Cakes Today

author: Jennifer Osasere Iguodala
reviewBody: I wasn’t happy with their service. I ordered the cake from Canada for someone in the U.K. to be delivered August 13th. I sent messages to confirm the order, and I was told it was still on track. Day of delivery, I waited till about 6pm GMT+1, it wasn’t delivered. So I sent another message and they said it was just delayed. It never came. I sent a message the next day and they claimed to have attempted delivery and failed but the recipient didn’t get any call. I was upset obviously and asked for a refund but they refused. Said the person had to go pick up from a local store which wasn’t feasible at the time because he’s new in Ashford, does not drive and has a very busy schedule. I paid 52£ in total for that cake. I begged for a reattempt on delivery, they said it couldn’t be done. Flash forward September 7th, the cake just randomly showed up! A good 3weeks later and they expected someone to steal eat it? I didn’t get any message from them, apologies nothing.... not an experience I’d like to go through again..

author: sonaliiib
reviewBody: My family and I have used Cakes Today twice now. They truly are very talented in designing their novelty cakes. Having many vegetarians in the family who do not eat egg, it is also an added bonus that their cakes are eggless but still just as delicious. The first cake ordered was a graduation cake for a pharmacist, the cake was designed by my sister. They added their own twist while sticking to the theme and the cake looked spectacular. The creative streak is what I love about Cakes Today! Please see photo attached. The pharmacy themed cake was complete with edible prescriptions, pills, a graduation hat and many more details. It was a hit! The second cake was an engagement cake; again the design was sent over. The price quoted was a little steep for us but after a quick consultation, changes were made to create a cake within our budget - another plus point. The only disappointing thing was that the "congratulations" was missing an S! And so they cake read "Congratulation on your engagement" - this was slightly annoying as when it was delivered it was too late to be changed as it was the day of the party. However it was hardly noticeable and we still thoroughly enjoyed the cake. Please see photos of the cakes attached. All in all, a brilliant company that makes every effort to cater to your needs. Will definitely be using them again.
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: Hetal Modashia
reviewBody: The cake that I ordered didn’t really live up to my expectations due to the colour not being as shown in the picture they display on their website as well as barely visible and not even being able to taste the premium filling that was ordered. I think customers should be made aware that the filling would be around half a centimetre between around 2 inches of cake which is not really much considering the size of the cake. I had ordered a navy blue giant cupcake as had seen on their website; however, I received a blue cake where the colour transferred and stained the skin. I was not made aware of this. Also, where the name was written, it had not been written properly or centred so therefore the same amount of space was not given on each side which was also disappointing. However, I gave the rating 3 stars due to the friendly service that I received where I called the company numerous times and received good advice and opinions on the cake.

reviewBody: DO NOT ORDER FROM DELIVEROO APP FROM HERE!! - Ordered through deliveroo, however they have their own riders so basically all them. It was my mother's birthday and did not have a chance to get a cake because of Covid, thought we would surprise one by ordering one! Order time took was estimated to be 50 minutes (long time, but worth it for a vegan cake...). 50 minutes passed and no sign even though it was out for delivery, so I messaged devlieroo. They informed me the company said it would take 45 minutes longer. A bit of a shock, however, a number of reasons could have factored for this delay so I understood. 2 hours passed - 'your order has been delivered' - NO ORDER!! TOOK ALL MY MONEY. Deliveroo said to contact them and offered no refund, and they of course have closed for the night(not their fault I suppose). Just wanted to let you all know, get the cake from the shop, because their drivers won't deliver the cake. PS. Wanted to give zero stars but that is not an option.

author: Kam Singh
reviewBody: So I decided to surprise a cake for my fiance and I wanted to make it as special as possible. I personalised the cake by sending them a picture of a cake I wanted them to make. I requested that the internal, sponge and jam should be black forest as that's her favourite. The cake surprisingly turned out very pretty and just as I wanted it to be. The colours were done to perfection, I was satisfied. My fiance was very surprised and she couldn't believe how irresistible it looked. However, there's some things I wasn't happy with; as I requested internal being black forest, it didn't taste like black forest. There was only one layer of cherry jam and that was the lowest layer. I was very disappointed as It didn't taste like black forest but more just normal chocolate sponge with no cherry jam. I feel like the cake could've tasted better. I was also extremely unhappy with the delivery driver. I wanted this to be a surprise. The driver called as I was driving and my fiance was sitting in the car as well so he was on loud speaker. He rung to confirm where I lived instead of knocking on the door knowing he was at the right place. The surprised was completely ruined. The Three stars are only for presentation otherwise it would be 2.
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: Zermin Alibhai
reviewBody: I ordered a surprise delivery 2 days prior to valentines for my family through Uber eats! The cake was supposed to have been delivered at 10am! At 10am on Uber it showed the order was still being prepared! I waited till 11am and contacted the company on website and sent multiple messages but no one replied. At 1pm Uber showed it as delivered and so I called the company and they said they are not using Uber and are running late on order but it’s out. At 4pm We called again, and they said they would deliver by 8pm (Uber still shows as delivered). I told them the kids would be asleep by 8 so to come before 8pm. They said they would try. It’s now almost 8:30pm and they still didn’t deliver. I wrote to Uber and Uber said this company elected not to use Uber drivers and wanted to use their own. So Uber is not at fault. Well, that’s just fraud! I paid for Uber eats services! I wrote to them on Instagram and all they did was apologize! They ruined my family’s valentine surprise! The most disheartening experience! Can’t believe they are still in business after all this fraud! Guys they cheat you, they pretend to use Uber eats services but they aren’t! So your delivery will never be guaranteed and nor on time! We didn’t get ours! Beware before ordering delivery from them!! They are Fraud, unprofessional, and inconsiderate!
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: Anna Rogers
reviewBody: Sadly a very bad experience. They advertise themselves the next day delivery cake shop, however once I placed the order, they emailed me saying that can only deliver 4 days later (the order was placed for an Easter treat in time for Easter for a family I cannot visit due to lockdown). Obtaining a refund is also extremely problematic - apparently Cakes Today is the only company that cannot issue refunds for orders placed online when billions of businesses do it on a daily basis. I contacted PayPal (who I used used as a payment method) and I was told that if they accept PayPal then refunds are very straight forward. Please do not use this company. I only now started reading the reviews on them and this is the scam they run and many people have been affected. They don't deliver on times or not at all and refuse to issue refunds! I wish I had read the reviews before I ordered from them. I reported them to a few organisations including PayPal and next they will will hearing from the law practice I work for.
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: Amanda Powell
reviewBody: EDIT: after posting this review, I was emailed promptly and told i would be issued a refund. Funny isn’t it. I have received said refund, for the cost of the cupcakes (£35.00), which leaves me having paid £1.50 for a letter in an envelope. — Am going to try to keep this short and sweet, which is going to be challenging as this was not a short OR sweet experience. I was transferred to Cakes Today by their sister company "Only Eggless", in my search to find a (vegan) bakery that could deliver to Seaford (next to Brighton). Cakes Today confirmed they could do it and the order was initiated over the phone. The order was then moved to email where all details were confirmed. Communication was prompt, which i appreciated. The box of 6 cupcakes cost £35.00 + i asked for a gift note to be included (which every other bakery I have ever used - about 15 different ones worldwide - have done at no additional cost), Cakes Today would charge an additional £1.50. So be it. The order was meant to be a birthday delivery for a colleague (I am the office manager for the company, so i do this quite a bit). The order was confirmed on the 24th of July and "delivered" on the 31st. I had to chase for a week to receive an invoice/receipt. Once received, the invoice was incorrect and missing major details (for example, the additional £1.50 i was charged for a "letter in an envelope", in lieu of a gift note.) I had to chase for the correct/amended invoice to be sent as well. The cupcakes arrive on the 31st .... and i think the attached photos speak for themselves. I was absolutely speechless. Imagine opening a cupcake box on your birthday and seeing this atrocity?! Unbelievable. The beat up box the cupcakes had travelled in ... was from a Crayola delivery - where did this box even come from? I immediately contacted Nikki from the Land of Cake/Cakes Today "Contact Centre" as she had helped me through the whole order process with prompt email replies. I expressed me disbelief with this delivery/service and requested a refund as the product they promised to be delivered was inedible/a nightmare. After a lot of back and forth and NO commitment to issuing a refund, she advised they could issue a free delivery of cupcakes. Great! Of course, i requested the cupcakes should just be a repeat order of the failed birthday delivery. NO RESPONSE. i follow up. no response. i follow up 5 more times over the course of 7 days and still no response. Finally someone called Joyce replied to me and says a callback has been arranged for Monday - 3 days from that date. "Great, I am on holiday, but kindly arrange for another day", No response. After such a horrible experience, you'd think there would be some ownership and customer service, but nothing. Unbelievable experience for an insanely expensive price for a box of 6 cupcakes. I would never use this service again and i highly encourage anyone who is thinking of using this service to try anywhere else first. x
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: Polycare
reviewBody: Positive: Professionalism , Quality , Responsiveness
name: Cakes Today

author: sindy seedam
reviewBody: Am am an existing customer who has completely been disappointed by your cake delivery service on the 20.10.2020. Recap: I ordered a cake , heart balloon and a card on 15.10.20 with Lakshan ravikumar. Picture of cake , card and balloon was sent on whatsapp(refer to attachment). The order was completed on call from the same guy. It was a free delivery but i requested if the cake could be delivered by 5pm as its an office... he told me he will try his best. i mentioned that last time you guys tried ur best and it was much appreciated. On 20.10.20 by 16.45 the cake wasnt delivered yet which i understood happens as its a free delivery. I whatsapp your team and a certain chesea told me that it will be there at 18.30 soon. Unfortunately i had to mess up my surprise and tell my partner ' you know i have ordered a surprise cake for our anniversary for you but you will have to wait outside your office as they will come at 18.30' , spoiled my evening the surprise is no more a surprise. fair enough my partner waited by 18.45 nothing yet i called from mauritius to your advertised number a certain lady which i dont remember the name kept on telling me your delivery is till 20pm, we cannot call the driver after an irrelevant discussion of 15 mins she finally agreed to call the concerned team to trace the driver. and she tells me the cake will be there at 19.20 like seriously you believe i can make someone wait when your staff assured me that the cake is coming at 18.30. finally my partner had to leave the office reception. and they called my partner directly to reschedule the delivery date for Thursday. fair enough. to my great surprise to day the cake card and balloon had been delivered . On the cake picture published on the website the wording are wriiten with cream thus to avoid a mess on the cake i imagine. its a strawberry jam 6inch cake. to my great surprise today we received a cake with the wordings messy with the jam written with. a surprise indeed. 2nd thing you guys kept the cake since tuesday...fine with me but what about the strawberry on it you dont change it to fresh ones?how much does a strawberry cost??? the strawberry is dead on the cake near to be rotten, see the picture. last but not the least... i ordered for a beautiful anniversary card and you guys send me another card. I told lakshan what to write( refer to attachment). I would like to have a proper explanation about everything that i mentioned as firstly you guys ruined my anniversary secondly sending me things i didnt choose. no proper communication, slow to reply my queries after payment is done. replying me back rudely when i called. i am the customer i didnt ask for stars my dear i just expected a proper service for which i paid!!! no proper organisation despite i mentioned the cake to be delivered before 5pm, an exception could be made if i gave this timing its because of a reason (office close). Tell me not even an apology from your side and today i receive rotten strawberry and not the card that i ordered that also blank. is this the kind of service that you give???? Expecting a quick reply. Rgds. Sindy

author: Miss Bala
reviewBody: Definitely not worth it. I am not one to write negative reviews (I think this might be my first actually) however I do feel this one is particularly important. I ordered a cake for my sister’s birthday from abroad (due to covid I couldn’t spend it with her) and trusted the company to deliver it on my behalf. I had several issues. 1) It was delivered at the wrong time entirely - 11am when it was requested for 6pm so my sister actually opened the door to receive it herself and it ruined the surprise completely!! (I informed them that they needed to deliver it specifically at 6pm and they guaranteed me that 100%) 2) they MISWROTE THE MESSAGE so it didn’t even make sense! What’s the point in paying for a personalised cake when it is not even done correctly? I paid over £50 and expected quality as a result and did not receive it. 3) The icing on the cake was smudged and incomplete on one side - totally unprofessional! 4) They didn’t even offer a part refund - they simply asked if they could come and take the cake away again to edit (and could not guarantee what time I would get it back!) or give me a small discount on the next cake I would buy - I.e I had to spend more money with their company!!! I was really disappointed - maybe the company is ok for a basic simple cake but if you expect something special and cannot collect the cake to check exactly what they have given you PLEASE think again before ordering. I’m sure other people have had good experiences but this was so upsetting as I was relying on this being an amazing surprise since I could not celebrate my sister’s birthday with her due to COVID. Totally gutted and won’t be buying another one from them again.
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: Pavlin Penchev
reviewBody: Ruined birthday mood and surprise due to late delivery. Very disappointed! After paying £70+ for a cake, I had to rescue the party dessert by going to Sainsbury's after dinner to get a last minute replacement. The post-purchase experience dealing with their team was negative as they weren't sensible and did not seem to accept (and take the responsibility for) their logistical and order-placing process issues. THE STORY: I ordered a birthday cake and agreed a guaranteed delivery date and time slot (8am - 8pm) - a very wide delivery slot anyway, which should have rung a bell at the time. I think that if a cake is delivered towards the end of the slot, it is not very useful and helpful if the occasion you are celebrating is on that same day, but I was hoping that they will make it in the early hours of the day. Instead, they delivered the cake just before 9pm (on Sunday), using the traffic as an excuse!!! No advance lateness warning, no apology on delivery. I complained and asked for a refund, but the company did not honour it. They started to ignore my emails too. They claimed they had a clause in their Ts & Cs that they reserve the right to be up to 2 additional hours late - that means until 10pm!!! - how useful is that!!!??? Who needs a cake at 10pm!!!??? My issue is that they never warned me, of course, of a possible lateness or about this clause during the ordering process. They claimed they did, saying that their staff was trained to do so with every order, but when I asked for a proof of any kind that I was informed verbally (they record their calls) or in writing, they refused to provide such a proof. Every business can make a mistake. Dealing with customers is not easy, but what makes the difference and contributes to a positive customer experience and to building a good business reputation is how you handle situations like this and how you correct your mistake, if that is important to you, as a business. UPDATE: (written after I read the owner's response) The various responses by the business owner to different reviews seem canned and not very personal at all. It appears that they are trying to divert the attention from this public forum. I had already sent multiple emails to the email address quoted (and the owner knew that as they finally responded), but publicly, they are asking me to email them again, like they care to resolve the problem, LOL. Stay away from this company if you don't want to be disappointed on important family occasions!
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: Just Shan
reviewBody: Amazing service - cakes came the same day just hours after I order them regardless of the pandemic. Spoke to a lovely lady who made sure the cakes got to me before I left out and I got a text when they were a stop away! I ordered the strawberry cream cupcakes and they are honestly the best cupcakes I’ve ever had! The piping was immaculate, the cream was delicious - so light and creamy and not too sweet. The strawberries were fresh and juicy and the cake was light, fluffy and had just the right amount of jam in them! Thank you so much! Cannot wait to order again! Xxxxx

author: N Gros
reviewBody: I was wary of ordering a cake online at short notice, but I ran out of time to make my son's birthday cake, so I took a chance. I ordered the cake on Friday, specifically a plain red cake that I could finish decorating at home. When the cake arrived promptly at 10 am Saturday, I was a bit surprised. I was even more surprised to open the box and see that it exactly as specified and BEAUTIFUL. The color was rich and bright and the fondant was smooth and perfect, like you would expect from a high-end bakery. Finally, I was most surprised when we cut the cake and it was genuinely DELICIOUS. Everyone at the party devoured it. I would (and will) absolutely order from Cakes Today again. If I had one very small complaint it would be that the cake was way too big. I had told the person who took the order that I needed a round cake to feed 30 children and 15-20 adults and he recommended a 16" cake, so that's what I ordered. The cake was delicious and everyone had at least one piece if not two, but we barely got through half of it. A smaller size would have been less wasteful and cheaper for me. But that's a very minor issue in the scheme of things. Overall cake and service were FAB. Highly recommend!
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: Mrs Deniz
reviewBody: Me and my family are very much disappointed with the quality of the cake ordered for the 50th birthday on 21st March spending £200 for a Ferrero rocher cake which was not worth at all. The sponge inside the cake was soo dry and stale with no flavour of Ferrero rocher. We immediately informed through WhatsApp the concerned but in return we got a call on the 9th of April that they would compensate £20 credit for a £200 cake! Though we suggested in good faith to bake another cake for Easter but they refused with no positive response. I would never recommend cake today to anyone because they are only money minded, not quality minded and have no value for customers. It was a total disaster to celebrate a 50th birthday with such a stale dry cake which was thrown in the trash and also I do have images of the cake which I have sent to them as an evidence to prove but no positive response till today.

author: Ash Sánchez
reviewBody: Delicious cakes! I've order from here a few times (St Valentines and Birthdays occasions) the vegan cakes are just incredibly tasty. For non-vegan people it just tastes the same but a lot lighter! So good, and delivery is quick as they can deliver the SAME DAY even when I ordered a cake after 3pm! Very impressive! The only thing I'd wish it was different is that if you order a cake in advance for a specific date, you don't have the option to book a time slot for delivery, let's say 8am - 11am or 12pm - 3pm etc.. It's always 'anytime of the day' which makes it very difficult if you work and are not home, or if you have a celebration and don't want the cake to arrive when guests have already left... That's the only aspect of the service that I'm not happy about. It should have a time slot delivery option. The rest is great. Quality of cakes is oustanding and price a bit hight but reasonable compared to other similar bakeries.

author: Ernest Koduah Adu
reviewBody: A change of plans for my girlfriend's birthday meant I had to look for delivery options at the last minute (literally same day). Most places I went to could deliver at the earliest the day after the birthday and on the verge of giving up, I chanced upon Cakes Today on Google. With some hesitation, I tried the site and was amazed to see they could deliver that same day. I placed an order around dawn of the day and they called me in the morning to confirm the delivery. That spurred me on and I made another purchase. In a few hours they called again to confirm and actually merged my separate purchases into one delivery. They promised the delivery would be made by 6.30pm and they actually got it done by 6pm after sending me a message at 5.30pm. I know this is long but that's how impressed i was and in the end was happy to know she did enjoy the cupcakes and chocolates i ordered. Thanks so much for coming to my aid, Cakes Today. Great customer service and prompt delivery. Great cakes on top of that. Quite the combination.Will definitely recommend.
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: Heena Patel
reviewBody: I contacted Cakes Today initially for a same day cake delivery (which not many places do near me) but eventually went for next day delivery. Their customer service chat function is great and I could message someone on WhatsApp/call to discuss options. Once the order was finalised over the phone I was sent an email payment link as I preferred to pay online and check everything properly. My order arrived the next day at around 6.45pm. The presentation was lovely - I ordered 12 vegan classic cupcakes. Unfortunately, the texture of the cakes were very dense and not light and fluffy like I'd expect from professionally baked cakes. The icing was really nice and surprised me how light it was despite being vegan. Improvements could be: fluffy and light cupcakes as opposed to being dense. And a tracking service to monitor delivery on the day.

author: Natasha Wilson
reviewBody: Have been avoiding leaving this review but I've been chasing my refund since January with the worst customer service I have EVER seen, so left with no option. Their software was broken at the time of ordering - it auto-added 2 brownies to my basket, I put it back down to 1, it kept going back up to 2. I started a chat + sent an email the minute the purchase was complete to explain but they said I already agreed to T&Cs (no refunds, no exceptions). After refusing their credit offer, I asked in writing that they send both boxes since i've been charged. Yet, they sent 1. I also paid £10 for a pre 4pm delivery, they arrived at 5.30pm. The recipient said the brownies that did arrive weren't nice at all (how can you get brownies wrong?!) Horrendously expensive (£70 for 2 boxes of brownies, x1 box of truffles + cake topper) They have not yet refunded me my £17.99. I've called dozens of times, sent a screen shot of me requesting both boxes several time now but no one replies, on the phone they say someone will call me back, they don't. I will keep trying. It's daylight robbery. Don't bother asking me to email experience@cakestoday as i've done that already. Do not ignore 130+ people leaving a 1* review and counting, it is not an accident.
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: Dana
reviewBody: I ordered cupcakes for same day delivery as I am in self-isolation and could not go out to buy a birthday cake. I ordered at 8am and they were delivered at 8pm. They were the best cupcakes I ever had: full of flavour, not sickly sweet, fresh. The frosting was creamy but not buttery and the filling in the middle of the sponge was a stroke of genius. Black gateau x2 Mango and passion fruit x2 Ferrero Roche x2 Thank you to Robert for making them, I will definitely order again as I am keen to try new flavours as well as have these again. UPDATE: So, I placed another order and tried the exotic flavours cupcakes as well as the original ones. The new box was awful, literally inedible, the sponge was heavy like a rock and not properly cooked. I called Cakes Today and they send me a replacement box of the original one I really liked - they were perfect again!! I think Cakes Today need to sort our some consistency issues with their standards but this goodwill gesture goes a long way and I will order from them again.
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: Caroline De Sousa
reviewBody: ORDER 151352. If I could rate this cake a zero, I would. I placed an order for my birthday cake a day in advance...delivery was free. I wasn't present when the cake was delivered but when I saw the cake....firstly, the box it came in was not close, or sealed like most cakes delivered are. Secondly, the cake had slid from the delivery, it wasn't centered and one side of the cake was completely leaning onto the box which looked horrible when we took the box away to slice the cake. I had ordered a vegan cake due to my babys allergies and I specifically asked what the cake would be like....the person I spoke to guaranteed the cake would be so light and fluffy. This wasn't the case. As I cut into the cake, the writing was already leaking and didn't look fresh at all, but I could feel every hard layer as I cut into the cake. The layers were completely uneven and the cake itself was not even. You could see where they added a ton of cream just to fill the holes and flat sides. The overly cooked crusts was still on the cake. The sponge itself was anything but light and fluffy. It tasted like a very hard madeira cake that someone had baked at home. Honestly, I'm so disappointed with the company and their overpriced cakes. I paid Close to £47 for a 10" excuse of a cake that my 10 year old could do a better job of baking. If I could get my money back I would buy unfortunately I think this is how this company makes its money. Speaking to another friend of mine, she had the same experience. Horrible, hard, stale disgusting cake! I didnt even bring it home. Waste of my money and total let down for my birthday.
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: Isamara Pereira
reviewBody: DO NOT LET THEM SCAM YOU! READ FOR ADVICE ON HOW TO GET A FULL REFUND. Avoid like the plague! I ordered a vanilla sponge with vanilla cream cake and received a chocolate sponge with chocolate cream. I obviously was not aware of this until after we sang happy birthday and cut the cake. I immediately called this company to reject this product but the customer adviser refused to collect it because it had been cut. I wrote an email complaining and requesting a full refund and their response was an absolute joke. It is UK law to receive a full refund under the consumer rights act if the product is not as described/faulty or not fit for purpose (as long as it is rejected immediately and within 30 days) so do not take no for an answer!!! They initially offered me £25 credit, then a partial refund, then £20 credit and finally £50 credit to use on their website. After various phone calls and threatening to contact the Financial Ombudsman Service (FOS), which I was more than willing to do since I had all the evidence (email of complaint, invoice, proof of cake as described on their website and invoice, proof of actual cake received). Only then, did they give my full refund. After 7 working days, I still had not received the actual refund so contacted them again and surprisingly received it the very next day. I assume at this point, they just wanted me to stop hassling them. If you would like to receive your money back then tell them you’ll contact FOS (advise strongly to do so if required) and also contact your bank under disputed transactions, as you can make a claim to reverse the transaction. Furthermore, I later realised that the cake I was given was clearly not fresh as the icing had looked more cream than white, the cake was extremely dry and the message on the board had clearly been wiped and replaced with a new happy birthday message. To add to that, my mum found a long disgusting black hair embedded in the cake. Hence, after reading all these terrible reviews of people being scammed, I am more than happy to help to get your money back. I will attach a cover email that you can use to complain. PS: please remember that what they are doing is not lawful and under UK law you have the right to a refund regardless of their terms and conditions. Just google Consumer Rights Act 2015 – returning goods. DO NOT LET THEM SCAM YOU OUT OF POCKET!!! Dear Sir or Madam, Reference: Consumer Rights Act 2015 I am writing with regards to the (product) I purchased from you on (date) for (£x) which is not to satisfactory quality due to the fact that the product is (not as described/faulty/not fit for purpose). On (date), I spoke to a customer adviser to make an order for (product). However, I instead received (explain issue further). Further details to support my complaint are enclosed, (with photographic evidence, receipt of purchase including the invoice and evidence of the description of the product advertised as such). The Consumer Rights Act 2015 states that goods should be as described, of a satisfactory quality and fit for the purpose. As the above item is not as described, you are therefore in breach of contract and I would like to reject the goods and request that you issue me with a full refund of (£x) as I am notifying you of my short-term right to reject within 30 days of receiving the goods. As a consequence of the faulty product, I had to (can be used to describe any actions you took) Additionally, I called Cakes Today upon discovering this fault and (they rejected to collect it/replace it etc). I look forward to a full response to my letter within 14 days. Yours faithfully,
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: ARUN ASOKAN
reviewBody: I had ordered a Sonic the Hedgehog themed cake from Cakes Today on the 17th of Jan 2019 for my son's 5th birthday. I was supposed to pick up the cake on the 20th Jan at 9 AM. I was promptly there at 9 AM and they asked me to wait for the cake as they were putting on the finishing touches (fair enough!). I waited till 9.45 when they sent someone to the bakery to find out what was going on. Fast forward to 10 AM when they brought the cake out (only 1 hour late) and announced that there was bad news. The sonic themed cake unfortunately did not have Sonic or any of the characters on it. They could do, Super Mario or Angry birds. I said I had paid for Sonic and my son would be devastated not to have his favourite characters. So they said they could print out the characters and stick them on icing shapes as an alternative. And it would take another 30 mins for this. I had no option but to accept as we had booked a party session at a local leisure centre at 10.30 AM. They said they would deliver the cake to our home by 10.30 (No compliments for the colossal messup, no offer of refund or reduction). Cut forward to 10.30, we are waiting for the cake to get going, it hasn't arrived. I call up Cakes today and obviously I am fuming and I say that my order hasn't turned up and the guy disconnects my call. The cake did arrive in another 10 mins but we ended up getting to the venue late and I have attached the photo of how the cake should have looked as per their website and how it looked at my poor son's party. At £60 odd you would expect better service and more professionalism.
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: Alison Renwick
reviewBody: Terrible customer service so this should be improved in the first instance. In the second instance they need to reassess their processes or ensure their delivery provider is well aware of what order should be delivered where. I ordered a Christmas Hamper for my sister in law but instead got one round (pineapple?) cake delivered with a yellow 'happy birthday' message on the top. My sister in law wasn't expecting an order as I had ordered it as a surprise Christmas gift for her family so she accepted the cake then checked with me on the order later. As I'm located in New Zealand, I'm on a different time zone. I've emailed the Cakes Today support team twice as well as communicated by text and still 2 and a half weeks later nobody has contacted me to apologise, to explain what went wrong or to offer to rectify the mistake. Very poor service and I would suggest you find another supplier if you don't want a special day or surprise to be ruined.

The delivery guy reminded me it was covid and that he can't be going up and down tower blocks. He was totally correct. I humbled myself and delivered it to my neighbour myself. They said it was delicious and beautiful. So I ordered it for about£23 . It arrived less than 24hours later downstairs. was delicious AND there was a sample of the Ferrero Rocher cake. .. what a nice touch! That's quite some service isnt it.. author: Aya Matsushita
reviewBody: Ordered 6 cupcakes at 19.45 on Saturday 27th and was informed they would be delivered by 10pm, they were not delivered until 00.30am. After a 4 hour 45 minute wait, they were extremely disappointing. Stale and, for some reason, very cold as if they had been refrigerated for a long time. My partner was so pi**ed, he dumped them straight in the bin. Cakes today used to be good, a few years ago you could order on the same day and receive freshly baked cupcakes that were soft, spongy, fresh and double the size of the ones we received yesterday, and cheaper, and you wouldn’t have to wait 5 hours for them. I think Cakes Today have become too ambitious and are taking on too many orders and so quality is suffering. Plus they really seem on that money grab, reducing the quality and size of product for some petty cash. I’m just glad we ordered off deliveroo and received a full credit to cover the failure we received last night. Don’t bother with your copy and paste response, we will not be ordering from here again, ever.
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

reviewBody: Given the other positive reviews I can only expect that there was a misfire somewhere. This £87 cake was promptly thrown in the bin. The cream cheese icing was definitely not cream cheese and tasted like whipped cream. As for the sponge, it was red... but that's about it. They got the food dye right but there was no hint of chocolate flavour, incredibly bland. To say that we were disappointed with this birthday cake is an understatement and we won't be buying another cake from them. The other reviews seem very positive so hopefully this was a one off. Unsurprisingly there's been no follow up from Cakes Today. Despite the post below from the 'owner's.

author: Kingston Foo
reviewBody: We are very surprised CakeToday have been given so high rated reviews from the public. And we have had a very unpleasant, frustrated and disappointed experience with them. We wont even give them 1 star. Our Aunt from Singapore ordered a cake on 2nd May 2020, and paid for express sameday delivery to deliver the cake to us in London. But the cake never arrived, so she contacted the customer service FROM SINGAPORE on 7th and 8th of May 2020, but customer service promised would investigate and get back to her. However she heard nothing back from the customer service team. So From 9th of May 2020 until 12/05/2020, we have been calling their customer service every day, spoken to their delivery team, customer service, adviser, customer complaint team, we have been given their names Luke, Anna, Joyce. Over the phone we have been advised, according to their record, the cake was delivered on 2nd of May, but we did not receive the cake, so they promised will investigate and get back to us with a solution. But we never hear from them. And every time we called we spoken to different people. On 11/05/2020 morning, we spoken to Luke, and he promised to get back to us with a solution on 11/05/2020 by 10pm, we were looking forward to hear from him. But we heard nothing from him. We don't mind if he contacted us and gave us an update if he couldn't come up with a solution, but we never hear from him. That was very incompetent customer service. Base on my personal experience, if you wanted to place any cake order with them, you will be very lucky if the cake delivered to you. If the cake went missing, they will not handle your issue in the correct and professional way. And those promises they said will get back to you just to make you walkaway, the next time you call, another person will give you the same response. Obviously in our case, they FAIL to deliver our order but brought us only Frustration and Hugh Disappointment. It would be a lot easier and hassle-free to get a muffin delivered from ASDA.
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: Philip Lee
reviewBody: Excellent service and lovely cake - pretty much what you really need from a cake supplier. The process to order and arrange delivery was simple and straightforward. Arrived on time which is really important for birthday cakes. Would advise to deliver the day before to be sure of timing but they deliver 7 days a week. The chocoholic cake was delicious, particularly the buttercream which was light and not too sweet and sickly. Still very rich so avoid massive slices :). The presentation was super, looks amazing covered in chocolate pieces such as kinder bueno, kitkat, maltesers, oreos, rocher etc. Only flaw in my opinion, the sponge was a little dry and dense, should be moist and light but otherwise a lot of people wouldn't notice, as the buttercream covers it up nicely. Bought on groupon discount so good value, full price is a little high. Overall, would recommend though
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: Chan Rathod
reviewBody: This is the first time I used a cake delivery to send to my family on Sunday. They were professional and helpful. There was a slight hiccup and I am so very grateful they did everything possible to make it right and I will definitely use them again, the cupcakes and doughnuts my family received were satisfactory. The main reason I would use them again is they care about their customers and the feedback is also acted upon. The cakes were lovely too. I will definitely recommend to my friends and family. Thank you
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

author: Akbar Hussain
reviewBody: I required a last minute cake with a baby shark theme and cakes today delivered in less than 24 hours which is crazy to believe but it's true! I was contacted promptly after leaving a message and when it came to ordering the cake, they ensured that i still got the cake I wished for whilst keeping to my budget. The free delivery offered to cover the vast majority of London and Essex is amazing and another added bonus in being able to order a cake from the comfort of your home without even having to leave the house. When the cake arrived it was exactly how I imagined it to be and when it comes to taste, everyone thoroughly enjoyed it. We spent a little bit extra to get the lindt lindor flavour and it was definitely worth it. Friends and family that came wanted to know right away where our cake was ordered from and without hesitation we recommended cakes today. The only negative was that the blue icing left everyone's tongues, fingers and any other surfaces stained with blue. So I would ask that less colouring is used but at the same time the kids did like the fact that their tongues and fingers had stained blue! I would definitely order again so thank you cakes today for making my first order with you a pleasant experience and for providing a cake that made my sons birthday a special celebration.
name: Cakes Today
address: Rubicon House, Second Way, Wembley, United Kingdom

reviewBody: I wanted a cake last minute (2days before event) and Cakes Today were able to help me out. Their enthusiasm and offers were there only to please the customer. author: Richard Kalas
reviewBody: Cakes Today delivered what looked like a cake, yet inside was the most disgusting and flavourless, artificial foam sponge. It was translucent white ! Reminiscent of builder's foam! The company hide behind their T&Cs and state that "taste" is subjective. This was an expensive cake. I post these pictures so that everyone can see the quality of their product. The artificial flavours are still lingering in my mouth as an insidious reminder of those two slices we endured. I have offered to return the remainder to their Wembley offices so that they can share in the delight of such "subjective" taste. This is as bad as bad gets. AVOID THIS COMPANY ! They ruined a very special occasion with this culinary travesty - and worse of all they do not care.

author: Lawrence Grant
reviewBody: What an amazing service Cakes Today provide! Having spoken to Karsh Patel (from Cakes Today) on a Friday afternoon about a National Citizen Service charity event that the firm I work for (Lawrence Grant, Chartered Accountants) was involved with, I was blown away how quickly he prepared the order and agreed to donate 70 cupcakes, and then personally deliver them to the event on Sunday morning himself. He sent us photos of the cakes, which looked absolutely incredible, and the NCS team were so chuffed that someone had gone to such great lengths to help support their fund raising event. We are delighted that we have such a strong relationship with Karsh & his team, and will absolutely continue to order from them again for future events and be spreading the word of the incredible service they offer at very reasonable prices, and the charitable work they do.

author: Aliya Zaidi
reviewBody: Tasted these today and pretty sure they are not fresh at all. They tasted like shop bought cupcakes with the butter cream added. When you look at the ingredients, there are many e numbers and not fresh ingredients. The company is claiming it is a fresh product but then ingredients contain preservatives. Why would a fresh product contain preservatives and so many e numbers? Very suspicious. Moreover, quite dangerous as there are some allergies to preservatives. I have family members who can eat freshly baked goods but not preservatives and I would have bought this thinking the cakes are made fresh. They certainly don't look or taste as if they are freshly made - and the ingredients list seems to suggest that they are anything but. It is strange there are so many artificial ingredients for a supposed freshly made product.

author: Lady Gigi
reviewBody: I was a bit dubious about ordering as I read some mixed reviews and upon contacting them initially they were very slow to confirm my order. But they did get back to me and apologised for the slow response. They let me know that they were overwhelmed with an increase of last minute orders because of the current COVID situation. They also offered me a discount for the inconvenience So i went ahead and booked and for a turnaround order with a very specific design with less than 48 hours notice, i was very impressed with the outcome. It was for my cousins birthday whom i could not see because of lockdown. They gave me a time frame of 11am-8pm. In the end it arrived at 8:30pm but they sent texts on the day of delivery and an update when the driver was on his way. The cake itself was really light and spongy with alot of cream (vanilla cream i think) it was tasty (i got sent a slice from my cousin!) it looked great and the most important thing is that she loved it. I will certainly order from these guys for a last minute occassion again.
